{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.13",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 13,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 13",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 13 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:1",
      "text": "“Lo, my eye has seen all this, my ear has heard and understood it.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:2",
      "text": "What you know, I also know; I am not inferior to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:3",
      "text": "But I would speak to the Almighty, and I desire to argue my case with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:4",
      "text": "As for you, you whitewash with lies; worthless physicians are you all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:5",
      "text": "Oh that you would keep silent, and it would be your wisdom!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:6",
      "text": "Hear now my reasoning, and listen to the pleadings of my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:7",
      "text": "Will you speak falsely for God, and speak deceitfully for him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:8",
      "text": "Will you show partiality toward him, will you plead the case for God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:9",
      "text": "Will it be well with you when he searches you out? Or can you deceive him, as one deceives a man?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:10",
      "text": "He will surely rebuke you if in secret you show partiality.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:11",
      "text": "Will not his majesty terrify you, and the dread of him fall upon you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:12",
      "text": "Your maxims are proverbs of ashes, your defenses are defenses of clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:13",
      "text": "“Let me have silence, and I will speak, and let come on me what may.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:14",
      "text": "I will take my flesh in my teeth, and put my life in my hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:15",
      "text": "Behold, he will slay me; I have no hope; yet I will defend my ways to his face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:16",
      "text": "This will be my salvation, that a godless man shall not come before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:17",
      "text": "Listen carefully to my words, and let my declaration be in your ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:18",
      "text": "Behold, I have prepared my case; I know that I shall be vindicated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:19",
      "text": "Who is there that will contend with me? For then I would be silent and die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:20",
      "text": "Only grant two things to me, then I will not hide myself from thy face:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:21",
      "text": "withdraw thy hand far from me, and let not dread of thee terrify me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:22",
      "text": "Then call, and I will answer; or let me speak, and do thou reply to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:23",
      "text": "How many are my iniquities and my sins? Make me know my transgression and my sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:24",
      "text": "Why dost thou hide thy face, and count me as thy enemy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:25",
      "text": "Wilt thou frighten a driven leaf and pursue dry chaff?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:26",
      "text": "For thou writest bitter things against me, and makest me inherit the iniquities of my youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:27",
      "text": "Thou puttest my feet in the stocks, and watchest all my paths; thou settest a bound to the soles of my feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.13.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:28",
      "text": "Man wastes away like a rotten thing, like a garment that is moth-eaten.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
